    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-04-17T08:35:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-04-16T20:00:00-05:00" n="887"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d887">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 867.4016/383</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The President of the Armenian National Delegation</hi>
                        (<persName corresp="#p_NB1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Nubar</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to President <persName corresp="#p_WW1" type="to"
                            >Wilson</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Translation]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date
                            ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content-and-sibling-dates"
                            calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1918-04-17T09:35:00-04:00"
                            notBefore="1918-04-16T21:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">undated</hi>
                        </date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received April 17, 1918, 9.35
                        a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Armenia is passing through the most tragic days of its history. The Turks, who
                    have already massacred nearly a million Armenians in Turkey, are reoccupying the
                    Armenian provinces abandoned by the Russians and invading the Caucasus itself,
                    threatening the two million Armenians of Russia. They are displaying anew their
                    implacable hatred of the Armenians, not only by fresh crimes, but also by their
                    treacherous zeal in spreading throughout neutral countries <pb facs="0979"
                        n="887" xml:id="pg_887"/> the foulest slanders against the Armenians,
                    charging them with perpetrating atrocities upon Musulmans, with the sole object
                    of attempting to excuse in advance the further massacres which they will not
                    fail to represent as justifiable reprisals. Therefore, in order to avert, before
                    it is too late, the final and fatal blow which will annihilate a Christian
                    nation, the Armenian National Delegation appeals to your holiest sentiments of
                    justice and humanity, proclaimed in your utterances which have been like the cry
                    of the conscience, not only of the American people, but of all civilized
                    peoples, to prevent the complete extermination of a whole people which has known
                    glorious days since the remotest antiquity and which, by its toil and its
                    natural gifts, has been the most potent civilizing factor in the East.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_NB1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Boghos Nubar</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
